{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_bMDZEzOrydzOBpdYQYFWHsyi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→schema: aidd.spec.v1\n     3→\n     4→# Core\n     5→status: draft\n     6→updated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\n     7→ticket: \"TST-001\"\n     8→slug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n     9→\n    10→owners:\n    11→  product: \"security-team\"\n    12→  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n    13→  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n    14→\n    15→sources:\n    16→  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n    17→  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n    18→  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n    19→  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n    20→\n    21→spec_pack:\n    22→  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n    23→  non_goals:\n    24→    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    25→    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    26→    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n    27→  constraints:\n    28→    - \"Integrate with existing JWT-claims middleware (backward compatibility required)\"\n    29→    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    30→    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    31→    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n    32→  decisions:\n    33→    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE)\"\n    34→    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = custom JWT-claims middleware\"\n    35→    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    36→    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    37→    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n    38→  risks_top:\n    39→    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    40→    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    41→    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n    42→  links:\n    43→    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n    44→\n    45→iteration_decisions:\n    46→  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    47→    scope:\n    48→      - api_contract\n    49→      - data_model\n    50→      - tests\n    51→      - roll_out\n    52→      - observability\n    53→    decisions:\n    54→      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n    55→      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n    56→      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n    57→    open_questions:\n    58→      - \"What is the exact database schema for existing users/roles tables?\"\n    59→      - \"Is there existing WebSocket infrastructure to extend?\"\n    60→\n    61→platforms:\n    62→  frontend:\n    63→    enabled: true\n    64→    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n    65→  backend:\n    66→    enabled: true\n    67→    stack_hint: \"Custom JWT-claims middleware\"\n    68→  mobile:\n    69→    enabled: false\n    70→    stack_hint: \"\"\n    71→\n    72→user_flows:\n    73→  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    74→    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    75→    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    76→    steps:\n    77→      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n    78→      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n    79→      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n    80→      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n    81→      - \"Frontend updates auth state without refresh\"\n    82→    edge_cases:\n    83→      - \"Insufficient admin permissions → 403 with audit log\"\n    84→      - \"WebSocket unavailable → graceful degradation\"\n    85→  - id: \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    86→    actors: [\"user\"]\n    87→    entrypoints: [\"POST/PUT/DELETE APIs\"]\n    88→    steps:\n    89→      - \"User attempts restricted action\"\n    90→      - \"RBAC middleware checks JWT claims\"\n    91→      - \"Access denied → 403 Forbidden\"\n    92→      - \"Attempt logged to audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\"\n    93→      - \"Frontend displays permission error\"\n    94→    edge_cases:\n    95→      - \"JWT token expired → 401 (not 403)\"\n    96→  - id: \"flow.live-session-update\"\n    97→    actors: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    98→    entrypoints: [\"WebSocket connection\"]\n    99→    steps:\n   100→      - \"User active in React app\"\n   101→      - \"Admin revokes role via API\"\n   102→      - \"WebSocket server broadcasts update\"\n   103→      - \"Redux store updates auth state\"\n   104→      - \"UI immediately hides restricted elements\"\n   105→    edge_cases:\n   106→      - \"Connection lost → exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   107→\n   108→ui_ux:\n   109→  screens:\n   110→    - \"Admin role management interface (existing)\"\n   111→    - \"Permission denied error display\"\n   112→  states:\n   113→    loading: [\"WebSocket connection status indicator\"]\n   114→    empty: []\n   115→    error: [\"403 permission denied message\", \"WebSocket connection error\"]\n   116→    partial_success: []\n   117→  accessibility:\n   118→    - \"Error messages must be screen-reader accessible\"\n   119→  i18n:\n   120→    - \"Permission error messages need i18n support\"\n   121→  analytics_events:\n   122→    - \"role_change_denied\"\n   123→    - \"permission_check_failed\"\n   124→\n   125→api_contract:\n   126→  - id: \"ALL POST/PUT/DELETE /*\"\n   127→    auth: \"JWT Bearer\"\n   128→    request:\n   129→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   130→      body_schema: {}\n   131→    response:\n   132→      success_schema: {}\n   133→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   134→      timeouts_ms: 5000\n   135→  - id: \"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"\n   136→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (admin only)\"\n   137→    request:\n   138→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   139→      body_schema:\n   140→        role: \"string\"\n   141→    response:\n   142→      success_schema:\n   143→        user_id: \"string\"\n   144→        new_role: \"string\"\n   145→        updated_at: \"timestamp\"\n   146→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"404 Not Found\", \"400 Bad Request\"]\n   147→      timeouts_ms: 3000\n   148→  - id: \"WS /ws/session\"\n   149→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (upgrade)\"\n   150→    request:\n   151→      content_type: \"N/A\"\n   152→      body_schema: {}\n   153→    response:\n   154→      success_schema:\n   155→        event: \"role_updated\"\n   156→        payload:\n   157→          user_id: \"string\"\n   158→          new_role: \"string\"\n   159→          timestamp: \"string\"\n   160→      error_codes: [\"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   161→      timeouts_ms: 30000\n   162→\n   163→data_model:\n   164→  entities:\n   165→    - name: \"audit_log\"\n   166→      fields:\n   167→        - \"id: UUID PK\"\n   168→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   169→        - \"action: ENUM(GRANT, REVOKE, DENIED)\"\n   170→        - \"target_resource: STRING\"\n   171→        - \"role_changes: JSONB\"\n   172→        - \"timestamp: TIMESTAMP\"\n   173→        - \"ip_address: INET\"\n   174→        - \"user_agent: STRING\"\n   175→    - name: \"user_sessions\"\n   176→      fields:\n   177→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   178→        - \"role: STRING\"\n   179→        - \"permissions: JSONB\"\n   180→        - \"last_updated: TIMESTAMP\"\n   181→  schema_changes:\n   182→    required: true\n   183→    notes: \"New audit_log table required; user_sessions cache table optional for performance\"\n   184→  versioning: \"backward\"\n   185→  idempotency: \"Role updates must be idempotent (same role set = no-op)\"\n   186→\n   187→tradeoffs:\n   188→  - topic: \"RBAC check caching strategy\"\n   189→    options:\n   190→      - name: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   191→        pros: [\"Fast (<10ms)\", \"Simple implementation\"]\n   192→        cons: [\"Stale data risk\", \"Per-node cache\"]\n   193→      - name: \"Redis distributed cache\"\n   194→        pros: [\"Consistent across nodes\", \"Configurable TTL\"]\n   195→        cons: [\"Network latency\", \"Additional infrastructure\"]\n   196→    decision: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   197→    rationale: \"Meet P95 <10ms latency requirement; accept eventual consistency for role changes via WebSocket push\"\n   198→  - topic: \"Session sync mechanism\"\n   199→    options:\n   200→      - name: \"WebSocket push\"\n   201→        pros: [\"Real-time updates\", \"Efficient\"]\n   202→        cons: [\"Connection management complexity\"]\n   203→      - name: \"Short polling\"\n   204→        pros: [\"Simple implementation\", \"No persistent connections\"]\n   205→        cons: [\"Higher latency\", \"Unnecessary load\"]\n   206→    decision: \"WebSocket push\"\n   207→    rationale: \"<5 second sync requirement demands WebSocket; polling would add unnecessary load\"\n   208→\n   209→risks:\n   210→  - risk: \"Performance impact from live RBAC checks on every request\"\n   211→    impact: \"high\"\n   212→    mitigation:\n   213→      - \"In-memory caching with TTL\"\n   214→      - \"Async audit logging\"\n   215→    detection:\n   216→      - \"RBAC latency P95 metrics\"\n   217→      - \"Alert if >10ms\"\n   218→  - risk: \"Session desync between backend and frontend\"\n   219→    impact: \"med\"\n   220→    mitigation:\n   221→      - \"WebSocket with heartbeat\"\n   222→      - \"Fallback to polling\"\n   223→    detection:\n   224→      - \"WebSocket connection metrics\"\n   225→      - \"Role mismatch logs\"\n   226→  - risk: \"Audit log storage growth\"\n   227→    impact: \"med\"\n   228→    mitigation:\n   229→      - \"Retention policy (90 days)\"\n   230→      - \"Archive to cold storage\"\n   231→    detection:\n   232→      - \"Storage usage monitoring\"\n   233→      - \"Growth rate alerts\"\n   234→  - risk: \"WebSocket connection instability\"\n   235→    impact: \"high\"\n   236→    mitigation:\n   237→      - \"Graceful degradation\"\n   238→      - \"Exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   239→    detection:\n   240→      - \"Connection uptime metrics\"\n   241→      - \"Error rate monitoring\"\n   242→\n   243→observability:\n   244→  logs:\n   245→    - \"RBAC check results (allowed/denied)\"\n   246→    - \"Audit log writes\"\n   247→    - \"WebSocket connection events\"\n   248→  metrics:\n   249→    - \"rbac_check_latency_p95\"\n   250→    - \"rbac_check_denied_total\"\n   251→    - \"audit_log_writes_total\"\n   252→    - \"websocket_connections_active\"\n   253→    - \"websocket_events_sent_total\"\n   254→  traces:\n   255→    - \"RBAC decision path\"\n   256→    - \"WebSocket message flow\"\n   257→  dashboards:\n   258→    - \"RBAC Performance Dashboard\"\n   259→    - \"Audit Log Activity\"\n   260→\n   261→roll_out:\n   262→  feature_flags:\n   263→    - name: \"rbac_live_enforcement\"\n   264→      description: \"Enable live RBAC checks on mutation APIs\"\n   265→    - name: \"websocket_session_sync\"\n   266→      description: \"Enable WebSocket session updates\"\n   267→  stages:\n   268→    - \"Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\"\n   269→    - \"Phase 2: WebSocket infrastructure\"\n   270→    - \"Phase 3: Frontend integration\"\n   271→    - \"Phase 4: E2E testing + performance validation\"\n   272→  rollback:\n   273→    - \"Disable feature flags\"\n   274→    - \"Revert to previous middleware version\"\n   275→\n   276→test_strategy:\n   277→  unit:\n   278→    scope:\n   279→      - \"RBAC middleware logic\"\n   280→      - \"JWT claims parsing\"\n   281→      - \"Audit log formatting\"\n   282→  integration:\n   283→    scope:\n   284→      - \"RBAC middleware + JWT integration\"\n   285→      - \"Audit log database writes\"\n   286→      - \"WebSocket connection handling\"\n   287→  contract:\n   288→    scope:\n   289→      - \"API response schemas\"\n   290→      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n   291→  e2e